<body>
<div class="wrap">

<header>
  <h1>📬 Email Automator — your setup checklist</h1>
  <p class="muted">A one-page walkthrough of everything <em>you</em> need to do to ship this on Vercel.
  Tick the boxes as you go — your browser remembers them across page loads.</p>
</header>

<div class="toc">
  <strong>What's in this page</strong>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="#prereq">Prereqs</a> (5 min)</li>
    <li><a href="#secret">Generate AUTH_SECRET + CRON_SECRET</a> (1 min)</li>
    <li><a href="#smtp">Gmail App Password for SMTP</a> (3 min) — required</li>
    <li><a href="#turso">Create the Turso database</a> (5 min) — required for Vercel</li>
    <li><a href="#groq">Get a Groq API key</a> (2 min) — optional</li>
    <li><a href="#google">Set up Google OAuth</a> (5 min) — optional</li>
    <li><a href="#vercel">Deploy to Vercel</a> (10 min)</li>
    <li><a href="#post">Post-deploy checklist</a></li>
    <li><a href="#self-host">Alternative: self-host on Linux</a></li>
  </ol>
</div>

<h2 id="prereq"><span class="step-num">1</span> Prereqs</h2>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p1" /><label for="p1">Node.js 20 or later installed (<code>node -v</code>)</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p2" /><label for="p2">Git installed; you have the repo cloned and ran <code>npm install --legacy-peer-deps</code></label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p3" /><label for="p3">A Gmail account with 2-Factor Authentication on</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p4" /><label for="p4">A Vercel account (free tier is fine) — <a href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank">sign up</a></label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="secret"><span class="step-num">2</span> Generate AUTH_SECRET + CRON_SECRET</h2>
<p>You need two long random strings. Run this twice on your laptop:</p>
<pre>node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"</pre>
<p>Save both somewhere temporary — you'll paste them into Vercel later.</p>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="s1" /><label for="s1">Generated AUTH_SECRET (64 hex chars)</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="s2" /><label for="s2">Generated CRON_SECRET (64 hex chars)</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="smtp"><span class="step-num">3</span> Gmail App Password for SMTP <span class="pill required">required</span></h2>
<p>Magic-link login and every outgoing email goes through SMTP. For Gmail:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Visit <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords" target="_blank">myaccount.google.com/apppasswords</a></li>
  <li>App: <em>Mail</em>, Device: <em>Other (Email Automator)</em> → Generate</li>
  <li>Copy the 16-character password (no spaces). Save it temporarily.</li>
</ol>
<div class="warn">⚠️ App Passwords require 2-Factor Authentication on your Google account. Enable 2FA first if it's not on.</div>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="m1" /><label for="m1">Have a Gmail App Password (16 chars)</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="turso"><span class="step-num">4</span> Create the Turso database <span class="pill required">required for Vercel</span></h2>
<p>Vercel is serverless — the local SQLite file won't persist. Turso gives you a hosted SQLite-compatible DB. The app's dual driver detects the URL and uses Turso automatically — no code changes needed.</p>

<h3>4a. Install the Turso CLI</h3>
<pre># macOS / Linux
curl -sSfL https://get.tur.so/install.sh | bash

# Windows (PowerShell)
irm get.tur.so/install.ps1 | iex</pre>

<h3>4b. Create the DB and grab the URL + token</h3>
<pre>turso auth signup        # one-time
turso db create email-automator
turso db show email-automator --url            # → libsql://email-automator-&lt;org&gt;.turso.io
turso db tokens create email-automator         # → eyJ…   (this is TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN)</pre>

<h3>4c. Apply migrations to the new DB (one-time, from your laptop)</h3>
<pre>DATABASE_URL=libsql://email-automator-&lt;org&gt;.turso.io \
TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=eyJ… \
npm run db:migrate</pre>

<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="t1" /><label for="t1">Created Turso DB; saved URL + token</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="t2" /><label for="t2"><code>npm run db:migrate</code> against Turso URL succeeded</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="groq"><span class="step-num">5</span> Get a Groq API key <span class="pill optional">optional</span></h2>
<p>Powers the <em>AI Improve</em> button in the template editor. Skip if you don't want that feature. Free tier covers light usage.</p>
<ol>
  <li><a href="https://console.groq.com" target="_blank">console.groq.com</a> → API Keys → Create</li>
  <li>Save the <code>gsk_…</code> key</li>
</ol>
<div class="ok">💡 Tip: you can also set this <strong>per-user</strong> from <code>Settings → AI</code> inside the running app, so you don't have to set the env var globally.</div>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="g1" /><label for="g1">Have a Groq API key (or skipping)</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="google"><span class="step-num">6</span> Set up Google OAuth <span class="pill optional">optional</span></h2>
<p>Adds a "Continue with Google" button on the login page. Magic link still works either way.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open <a href="https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials" target="_blank">Google Cloud → Credentials</a></li>
  <li>Create OAuth Client ID → <em>Web application</em></li>
  <li><strong>Authorized redirect URI</strong>: <code>https://your-vercel-url.vercel.app/api/auth/callback/google</code></li>
  <li>Copy the Client ID + Client Secret — they go in Vercel env vars below</li>
</ol>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="goo1" /><label for="goo1">OAuth client created; have ID + Secret (or skipping)</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="vercel"><span class="step-num">7</span> Deploy to Vercel</h2>

<h3>7a. Push your repo to GitHub (if not already)</h3>
<pre>git remote -v          # confirm origin points at your fork
git push origin main</pre>

<h3>7b. Import the project in Vercel</h3>
<ol>
  <li><a href="https://vercel.com/new" target="_blank">vercel.com/new</a> → Import Git Repository → pick this repo</li>
  <li><strong>Root Directory: <code>web</code></strong> (important — the Next app lives under <code>web/</code>, not the repo root)</li>
  <li>Framework Preset: Next.js (auto-detected)</li>
  <li>Don't click Deploy yet — set env vars first</li>
</ol>

<h3>7c. Paste these env vars in Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables</h3>
<button class="copy-btn" onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('env-snippet').textContent); this.textContent='copied!'; setTimeout(()=>this.textContent='copy',2000)">copy</button>
<pre id="env-snippet"># ── required ─────────────────────────────────────────────
AUTH_SECRET=&lt;the first secret from step 2&gt;
APP_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app
NEXTAUTH_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app
DATABASE_URL=libsql://email-automator-&lt;org&gt;.turso.io
TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=&lt;from step 4b&gt;
CRON_SECRET=&lt;the second secret from step 2&gt;
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=you@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=&lt;the Gmail App Password from step 3&gt;
EMAIL_FROM=Your Name &lt;you@gmail.com&gt;
ADMIN_EMAILS=you@gmail.com

# ── optional ─────────────────────────────────────────────
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=&lt;from step 6, or leave empty&gt;
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=&lt;from step 6, or leave empty&gt;
GROQ_API_KEY=&lt;from step 5, or leave empty — can set per-user later&gt;
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
DAILY_SEND_LIMIT=50
TIMEZONE=Asia/Kolkata</pre>

<div class="danger">🚨 <strong>Do NOT set <code>ALLOW_DEV_SIGNIN=true</code> in production.</strong> It bypasses authentication for any email on <code>DEV_BYPASS_EMAILS</code>.</div>

<h3>7d. Deploy</h3>
<p>Click <strong>Deploy</strong>. ~2 minutes. The first visit hits <code>app/(app)/layout.tsx</code> which auto-seeds 20 starter templates on your first sign-in.</p>

<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="v1" /><label for="v1">Repo imported with Root Directory = <code>web</code></label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="v2" /><label for="v2">All env vars from 7c pasted in Vercel</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="v3" /><label for="v3">Build succeeded; site is live at https://your-app.vercel.app</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="v4" /><label for="v4">Updated <code>APP_URL</code> + <code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code> + Google OAuth redirect URI with the real Vercel URL</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="post"><span class="step-num">8</span> Post-deploy checklist</h2>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p51" /><label for="p51">Visit <code>/login</code> → sign in via magic link (check Gmail inbox)</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p52" /><label for="p52"><code>/diagnostic</code> → "Run checks" → SMTP / Groq / SPF / DMARC all green or sensible warns</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p53" /><label for="p53"><code>/diagnostic</code> → "Send test to me" → email arrives within 10 s</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p54" /><label for="p54">Add yourself as a contact, activate a template, create + send 1 draft to yourself</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p55" /><label for="p55">Open that email → check <code>/analytics</code> shows 1 sent + (after a moment) 1 open</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p56" /><label for="p56">Edit <code>public/.well-known/security.txt</code> — replace the placeholder email with yours, push</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p57a" /><label for="p57a"><strong>Set up the cron via GitHub Actions</strong> (Vercel Hobby plan blocks 1-min crons). Go to <strong>GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions</strong> and add two repository secrets: <code>APP_URL</code> = your Vercel URL (no trailing /), <code>CRON_SECRET</code> = the same value you put in Vercel env vars. Then the included <code>.github/workflows/cron-tick.yml</code> will fire every 5 min.</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p57b" /><label for="p57b">Verify: <strong>GitHub → Actions tab → "Cron tick"</strong> — first run appears within 5 min of adding the secrets. Or click <strong>Run workflow</strong> for an immediate test. Green ✓ = working.</label></li>
  <li><input type="checkbox" id="p58" /><label for="p58">If you have a custom domain: update <code>APP_URL</code>, <code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code>, and the Google OAuth redirect URI to use it</label></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="self-host"><span class="step-num">9</span> Alternative: self-host on Linux</h2>
<p>If you'd rather not use Vercel, you can run on any Linux box with Node 20+. SQLite file persists locally.</p>
<pre>cp .env.example .env       # edit everything; leave DATABASE_URL as ./data/tracker.db
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
npm run build
npm run db:migrate
npm install -g pm2
pm2 start npm --name email-automator-web    -- start
pm2 start npm --name email-automator-worker -- run worker
pm2 save && pm2 startup</pre>
<p>Then point your nginx/Caddy at <code>localhost:3000</code>. Back up <code>./data/</code> with rsync/restic.</p>

<hr style="border:none;border-top:1px solid var(--line);margin:40px 0">
<p class="muted" style="text-align:center;font-size:13px">
  Stuck? Open the running app and visit <code>/guide</code> for the full manual.<br>
  Repo: <a href="https://github.com/Surya8991/Email-Automator" target="_blank">github.com/Surya8991/Email-Automator</a>
</p>

</div>

<script>
  // Persist every checkbox tick to localStorage so the checklist survives
  // page reloads. Pure client-side, no tracking.
  document.querySelectorAll('input[type=checkbox]').forEach((cb) => {
    const k = 'ea-setup:' + cb.id
    cb.checked = localStorage.getItem(k) === '1'
    cb.addEventListener('change', () => localStorage.setItem(k, cb.checked ? '1' : '0'))
  })
</script>
</body>
</html>
